Text.Value: Do you know where your killer was heading next?
What were you doing when you were killed?
*The corpse remains silent. It does not know.*

EditorData.logicalname: DOESN'T KNOW ANSWER - DELETE IF NOT NEEDED

Text.Value: Tasting wine... with Roger... Master Meztli...
Why did you have the orphanage?
War on... Children... Need a home...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*

Synopsis: If Dolor kills Cora with the ritual, not in the wine festival, we will have a SwD dialog with Cora to get some clues about her killer.
